race.comment: WIREWALKER (4) was beaten a neck here first-up over 1200m at this track. He's further improved and will be fitter for that run. Has a low gate and 2kg claim and can go one better. BENFICA LASS (7) is an improver from the Healey yard. Won at the Gold Coast first-up and missed a neck at Beaudesert following, and four winners have come out of that. Maps well and has weight relief. ESJAY (1) just missed here two back in a 78 but was plainer at Warwick as a $3.5F. He'll go a lot better back here and will come hard over the longer sprint. TIGON PRINCESS (6) resumed over 1200m at this track and was too good for her rivals. Open to plenty of improvement and jumping from the paint must be included. THE LOUVRE (2) has won three of his last four. This is a step up, but the 3kg claim brings her into it on a 7-day return.
